.TH VLP 1 "@DATE@" "@PROJECT_NAME@ @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.\"
.SH NAME
vlp \- inspect pacman.log for installed packages, sync commands, and upgrades
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vlp
.RB [ \-i | \-\-installed
.B |
.RB \-c | \-\-show\-commands
.B |
.RB \-u | \-\-upgraded
.B |
.RB \-s | \-\-show\-hist ]
.RI [ n ]
.br
.B vlp
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.br
.B vlp
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version ]
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B vlp
reads
.I pacman.log
(and, if present, its rotated counterpart, plain or gzip\-compressed) and
reports on recent package activity. Exactly one mode flag is required.
.PP
The optional argument
.I n
limits how many matching log lines are considered before deriving the
result (default:
.BR 5000 ,
subject to the compiled\-in default). For
.B \-\-installed
and
.BR \-\-upgraded ,
only the most recent action for each package within that window is used
to decide the package's current state.
.\"
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-installed " [\fIn\fR]"
Show packages that are currently installed according to the log, i.e.
whose most recent
.I installed
or
.I removed
event within the last
.I n
matching lines was
.IR installed .
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-show\-commands " [\fIn\fR]"
Show the last
.I n
user\-initiated
.B pacman -S
(or
.BR \-\-sync )
commands recorded in the log.
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-upgraded " [\fIn\fR]"
Show the last
.I n
package upgrade events, one line per package reflecting its most recent
upgrade within the window.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-show\-hist " [\fIn\fR]"
Show the last
.I n
pacman transactions, with installed/removed/upgraded/downgraded/
reinstalled packages grouped under the transaction they occurred in,
alongside the triggering command and timestamp when available.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display a usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Output version information and exit.
.\"
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B vlp
exits with status 0 on success. It exits with a non\-zero status and
prints a usage message to standard error if no mode flag, or more than
one, is given, or if the arguments are otherwise invalid.
.\"
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /var/log/pacman.log
The current pacman log.
.TP
.I /var/log/pacman.log.1
.TQ
.I /var/log/pacman.log.1.gz
Rotated pacman log, read before the current log if present.
.\"
.SH EXAMPLES
Show packages currently installed, based on the last 5000 matching lines:
.RS
.B vlp \-\-installed
.RE
.PP
Show the last 20 explicit sync commands:
.RS
.B vlp \-c 20
.RE
.PP
Show the last 50 upgrade events:
.RS
.B vlp \-\-upgraded 50
.RE
.PP
Show the last 10 transactions, packages grouped by transaction:
.RS
.B vlp \-s 10
.RE
.\"
